Over 10 million Indians have lost their jobs because of the second wave of Covid-19,
 and around 97 per cent of households have faced income loss since the beginning of the pandemic last year,
 Centre for Monitoring Indian Economy (CMIE) chief executive Mahesh Vyas said.

The unemployment rate measured by the think-tank is expected to come at 12 per cent at the end of May as against 8 per cent in April, Vyas told news agency PTI, adding this signifies that about 10 million or 1 crore Indians have lost jobs in this period.